1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
 Hrvod:Bog ima toliko toga za dati nam,Ne znam da li to sve uopće možemo primiti i shvatiti,Ali moramo negdje započeti,Ali moramo negdje započeti.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:30,000
 Mislim da je jedan element onoga što će biti večeras.

3
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
 Koliko god se vi trudite biti s Otcem,

4
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:44,000
 Ovi oko vas jednako toliko trude.

5
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:51,000
 Jedna stvar koja nam je zajednička ovdje večeras,

6
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
 Svi žele doći kući i kocu.

7
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 Svaki od nas.

8
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:06,000
 Mi svi smo na drugom mjestu u tom putovanju,

9
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 Ali svi smo na tom putu.

10
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
 I nekoliko puta smo spomenuli večeras,

11
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:25,000
 Kako bi trebali više biti na pomoć jedan drugome.

12
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:35,000
 jer ako svako od vas može posvjedočiti to je dugo putovanje.

13
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:42,000
 Mislim da moramo pronaći način kako pomoći jedan drugome.

14
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 I posvetiti se tomu.

15
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:55,000
 I think another aspect of our growing closer to the Father,

16
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
 Is a gift of repentance.

17
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
 I think often, particularly in the Catholic world,

18
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:13,000
 We perhaps misunderstand repentance sometimes.

19
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,000
 We often think repentance means

20
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,000
 I hate myself, I hate myself, I hate myself.

21
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:32,000
 I'm not sure that's the best understanding of repentance.

22
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:37,000
 Perhaps a more authentic understanding from scripture.

23
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:41,000
 Možda malo autentičnije svačanje koje proizlazi iz pisma.

24
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
 Repentance is realizing

25
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
 That you're a little bit off on the path.

26
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:54,000
 Pokajanje znači da svačanje da smo malo skrenuli s puta.

27
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
 But then it's turning around

28
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
 Ali onda se vraćamo nazad

29
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
 And walking the right path.

30
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
 I hodamo pravim putem.

31
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:08,000
 A lot of times we think of repentance as an emotion.

32
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,000
 Puno puta razmišljamo o pokajanju kao emociji, osjećaju.

33
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:16,000
 It's perhaps more accurate to think of repentance as a decision.

34
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,000
 Bolje razmišljati o pokajanju kao odluci.

35
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:23,000
 That is then followed by an action.

36
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:29,000
 I'll give you a case in point.

37
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
 Daću vam jedan primjer.

38
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 For those who are biological fathers.

39
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 Za one koji su biološki očevi.

40
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
 Or those who are teachers.

41
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
 Ili oni koji su, na primjer, učitelji.

42
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
 Those who are athletic coaches.

43
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
 Oni koji su treneri u sportu.

44
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
 Those who are priests.

45
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,000
 Oni koji su svećenici.

46
00:03:50,000 --> 00:04:06,000
 načine na koje sam pogriješio kao otac.

47
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:19,000
 Jer kada vidim koliko je savršen i koliko je lijep i koliko je njegova ljubav ogromna očeva.

48
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:25,000
 I can see so many imperfections in my fatherhood.

49
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:31,000
 And this is where the devil wants to come in.

50
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:37,000
 He's called the accuser of the brethren.

51
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:44,000
 And boy does he love to accuse us in this area.

52
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 As we have been together this weekend.

53
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
 Kako smo bili skupa ovaj weekend.

54
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
 I think we all have come to realize.

55
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 How deep this father relationship is.

56
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:01,000
 Mogli smo shvatiti koliko je duboka ova veza i odnos s ocem.

57
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:14,000
 I možemo shvatiti koliko smo propatili.

58
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:18,000
 Zbog toga što naš biološki otac nije bio ono što je trebao biti.

59
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:22,000
 So now as we're thinking about this.

60
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
 We're thinking.

61
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:30,000
 Maybe I haven't been a real good father.

62
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 And the devil says, "That's right, you're no good."

63
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 You're bad.

64
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:41,000
 You've actually damaged people.

65
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:46,000
 There's no place for you here.

66
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
 The truth is there is a place for you here.

67
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:56,000
 We are the sons of God.

68
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:02,000
 And we're in a transformative process.

69
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:09,000
 Is it John or Paul who talk about us being transferred from a glory to a glory to a glory?

70
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,000
 Here's what I hope.

71
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:26,000
 I hope tonight you are more open to the Father's love than you were one week ago.

72
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:43,000
 What I really hope is next Saturday night you'll be more open to the Father's love than you are right now.

73
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:53,000
 Are you okay, my brothers, with this being a process?

74
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:58,000
 Can you be patient with yourself just a little bit longer?

75
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:03,000
 Because God is patient.

76
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,000
 Because God is patient.

77
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:09,000
 Many of us are in a major transition.

78
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:23,000
 And I think it was my own son who said tonight that the best things don't just come like that.

79
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:27,000
 It's little by little, piece by piece.

80
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:40,000
 So, if you can accept that this is a process.

81
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:50,000
 The devil will lose power over us.

82
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:54,000
 Because he will not discourage us.

83
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:59,000
 But as I said, that's more of a decision than it is an emotion.

84
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:10,000
 So, what repentance is in the best sense of the word.

85
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:16,000
 It's recognizing something is off.

86
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:26,000
 It's choosing the right path.

87
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,000
 But then it's walking the right path.

88
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:33,000
 So, there's three steps to repentance.

89
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
 Tri su koraka u pokajanju.

90
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:39,000
 And sorrow may be a part of that.

91
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,000
 I tuga može biti dio toga.

92
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,000
 Žalovanje.

93
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 But sorrow is not all of it.

94
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,000
 Ali žalovanje nije cijela stvar.

95
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:51,000
 And sometimes it's easier to beat yourself up.

96
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:56,000
 But nothing changes.

97
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:04,000
 Do you remember our older brother Jesus gave us an example about two sons?

98
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:10,000
 Sviđate se kad nam je naš stari brat Isus dao primjer od dva sina.

99
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:15,000
 And one son was told by the father to go out and work in the fields.

100
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,000
 Jednom je rečeno da ode i radi u polju.

101
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 And the son just said, I'm not going.

102
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,000
 Sin je samo rekao, ne idem, neću iću.

103
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,000
 The second son said, I'll go.

104
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
 Drugi sin je rekao, ja ću, idem.

105
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
 I'm the good kid, I'm happy to help.

106
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,000
 Ja sam dobro djete, spreman sam pomoći.

107
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,000
 I think you're great father.

108
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,000
 Mislim da si super tata.

109
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,000
 Then the kid never goes anywhere.

110
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,000
 A djete nikad ne ode na posao.

111
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 In the meantime, the older kid had a change of heart.

112
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,000
 Umeđu vremenu, drugo djete je doživjelo promjeno u srcu.

113
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:53,000
 He realized he was wrong.

114
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:58,000
 And then he sat down all day on the couch and felt sorry for himself.

115
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:03,000
 I got that wrong, I got that wrong.

116
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,000
 He didn't sit on the couch and feel sorry for himself.

117
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:10,000
 He went out and went to work.

118
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 And Jesus says,

119
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:17,000
 It was the kid who had the bad attitude and changed

120
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:20,000
 who actually ended up doing the will of the father.

121
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:26,000
 Ono djete koje je imalo krivi stav, ali je doživjelo promjenu srca

122
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 je ono koje je izvršilo volju očevu.

123
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,000
 The other kids, I'm not saying all the right things.

124
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,000
 Drugo je govorilo sve prave stvari.

125
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 And nothing changes.

126
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:40,000
 So if you're willing to accept my definition of repentance,

127
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:45,000
 that it's an awareness,

128
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
 that it's a decision,

129
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 that it's a decision,

130
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
 and it's an action.

131
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,000
 If just for tonight you can accept that as our definition,

132
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 then this is a good moment for us to repent.

133
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:10,000
 Because if we don't repent,

134
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:16,000
 we carry this weight all with us everywhere we go.

135
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:21,000
 It's better to leave it here.

136
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:26,000
 Because the father wants to receive it from us.

137
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 I'm gonna tell you a little secret nobody else knows.

138
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:35,000
 I'm gonna tell you a little secret nobody else knows.

139
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 You can never surprise God.

140
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:44,000
 Don't ever try to make a surprise party for God.

141
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:51,000
 He already knows you're planning the party.

142
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 There is absolutely nothing that you could repent of.

143
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:03,000
 And God says: Whoa, I didn't see that.

144
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:07,000
 He's known forever.

145
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,000
 He's known forever.

146
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,000
 It's we are the ones who can't see it.

147
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,000
 We are the ones who can't see it.

148
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:19,000
 So there's this need to stand together, help each other.

149
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:27,000
 And there's a need of repentance.

150
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:33,000
 But there's also a need of acceptance.

151
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:38,000
 Have you ever met a person in your life

152
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 who won't let anybody do anything for them?

153
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:51,000
 They don't want anybody to do anything for them.

154
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:59,000
 Possibly they really don't want to trouble people.

155
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:13,000
 I would say most of the time it's probably an issue of pride.

156
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:19,000
 And I have to say this is particularly true with men.

157
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,000
 I don't want to be beholding to anybody.

158
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:27,000
 I don't want to be in debt to anybody.

159
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,000
 I'm my own man.

160
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:32,000
 I take care of myself.

161
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:42,000
 And many of us, even though we want the love of the Father,

162
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:47,000
 still are thinking we're going to get enough points

163
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:50,000
 to give him that he's obliged to love us.

164
00:13:50,000 --> 00:14:01,000
 In that case, it's not love freely given.

165
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:05,000
 I bought it.

166
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,000
 I bought it.

167
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 There it is God.

168
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:13,000
 What do I get back?

169
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:16,000
 I don't think we do it intentionally.

170
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:28,000
 But for a lot of us, it's extremely hard just to relax and let God love us.

171
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:39,000
 I don't know if we're trying to make up for past mistakes.

172
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:45,000
 I don't know if we're trying to prove something to ourselves.

173
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:51,000
 Maybe we are bargaining with God, I don't know.

174
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:58,000
 But friends, that really isn't love.

175
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,000
 That's business.

176
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:06,000
 I give you something, you give me something.

177
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:12,000
 I didn't do you a favor and you didn't do me a favor.

178
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
 We made a business transaction.

179
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:18,000
 And you and I are equals.

180
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:28,000
 To receive the Father's love, it's not equal.

181
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:32,000
 It's not fair.

182
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 It's not deserved.

183
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,000
 It's a gift from God.

184
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:53,000
 I mentioned to you earlier tonight this experience of carrying the cross across America.

185
00:15:53,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 And many times I had to be dependent on other people.

186
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:07,000
 And to be honest with you, it was embarrassing.

187
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:11,000
 I didn't always like it.

188
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,000
 But it's the way it was.

189
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:19,000
 Let me tell you one story about an uneven giving.

190
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 I was out in the New Mexican desert.

191
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:36,000
 I had about five or six other men walking with me that day.

192
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:44,000
 The temperature was about 114 Fahrenheit.

193
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,000
 It was terrible.

194
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:51,000
 And these men hadn't walked with me before.

195
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 So we had, you know, water and a little bit of food.

196
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 No support vehicles, no cars.

197
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 And we were just walking through the desert.

198
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 We were going to meet somebody in about 25 kilometers.

199
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 And they were going to bring us food and water.

200
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:23,000
 We never found the people.

201
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:26,000
 We never made the connection.

202
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:33,000
 At first it was very frustrating.

203
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:44,000
 But as the men got weaker and weaker, it became terrifying.

204
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 These men had blisters on their feet.

205
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 One man could no longer walk.

206
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 The sun was baking our brains out.

207
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 I really thought somebody was going to die that day.

208
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 It was one of the most frightening days of the entire trip.

209
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 We are in the middle of a desert.

210
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 And we just can't stand there and die.

211
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,000
 So we kept walking.

212
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:26,000
 We are going slower and slower.

213
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 We are weaker and weaker.

214
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 And I knew that we were getting close to a very critical moment.

215
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 And I remember whispering a prayer.

216
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:52,000
 God, if you don't save us, we will die.

217
00:18:52,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 I didn't pray that out loud because I didn't want to scare these men.

218
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,000
 I was terrified.

219
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 I looked down this path.

220
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 I looked down this path.

221
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:13,000
 And suddenly I saw two statues standing there.

222
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 I saw two statues standing there.

223
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,000
 We are in the middle of nowhere.

224
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,000
 What are these two statues doing here?

225
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 We are in the middle of nowhere.

226
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 What are these two statues doing here?

227
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,000
 They are standing right by the side of the road.

228
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,000
 Not moving.

229
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 They are standing right by the side of the road.

230
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,000
 Not moving.

231
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 And I said, what is that?

232
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 I said, what is that?

233
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,000
 They said, I don't know.

234
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 We have driven this road.

235
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,000
 We have never seen that before.

236
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 We have never seen that before.

237
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 As we got closer.

238
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:43,000
 They were not statues.

239
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
 They were two people.

240
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 A man and a woman.

241
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 A husband and a wife.

242
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:52,000
 They were Indians.

243
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 And they literally were wrapped in these heavy blankets.

244
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:03,000
 And they had something under the blanket.

245
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 And as we are walking by, they are just standing there.

246
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 So I kind of like, I thought they were statues.

247
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 I kind of walked over and looked at them.

248
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 And the woman says, hello.

249
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 I really thought they were statues.

